Description: Body sherd of Attic black-figured pottery closed vessel, perhaps oenochoe; exterior: black-figure decoration consisting of patterned drapery from a female figure's peplos (incised squares: small irregular incisions in some, faded colour dabs in some, at least one black only) with plain black either side, small reserved area on one corner.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0838) (Phase 1)
